name: .Net Developer
qualification: Complete a relevant qualification, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Information Technology.

name: Agile Business Analyst
qualification: Explore formal training options. There are many different courses depending on your interests and skills. Some options may include a Bachelor of Computer Science or a Bachelor of Information Technology.

name: Analyst Programmer
qualification: There are a range of different formal training options that provide an entry into the information technology industry, such as a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50115) or an Advanced Diploma of Information Technology Business Analysis (ICT60315).

name: Android Developer
qualification: Complete a relevant degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Software Engineering (Honours). This usually takes three to four years.

name: Backend Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification in Computer Science with a focus on Software Development.

name: Business Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in business, business analytics, information technology or a related field. This usually takes three years of full-time study.

name: Business Consultant
qualification: A Bachelor of Business may be an advantage when looking to become a Business Consultant.

name: Business Intelligence Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree majoring in computer science, data science, business or a related field. This is usually a three-year course of full-time study.

name: Business Intelligence Software Developer
qualification: Complete a Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Computer Science.

name: Business Systems Analyst
qualification: Complete a degree in information technology, information systems or business information systems such as a Bachelor of Business Information Systems.

name: Change Manager
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in business, business administration, commerce, change management or a related field.

name: Chief Information Officer
qualification: Complete a degree in computer science, software engineering or a related field. These are usually three-year course of full-time study, with prerequisites including completion of Australian Year 12 (or equivalent) and required units or assumed knowledge in English and mathematics.

name: Chief Technology Officer
qualification: Complete a degree in computer science, software engineering or a related field. These are usually three-year course of full-time study, with prerequisites including completion of Australian Year 12 (or equivalent) and required units or assumed knowledge in English and mathematics.

name: Computer Engineer
qualification:
Complete a qualification in computer engineering. This could be a 
Certificate IV in Information Technology (ICT40120), a 
Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) or a Bachelor degree majoring in computer engineering.

name: Computer Technician
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in information technology, computer science or a related field.

name: Cyber Security Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, cyber security, information technology or a related field.

name: Data Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in a relevant discipline, such as computer science, information technology, mathematics, statistics or business analytics.

name: Data Architect
qualification: Complete a Bachelor of Science (Data Science) or a Bachelor of Computer Science. This is a three-year course of full-time study.

name: Data Engineer
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science. This is typically a three–year course of full–time study.

name: Database Administrator
qualification: Complete a qualification in Information Technology. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (ICT40120), a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220), or a bachelor degree majoring in Information Technology.

name: Database Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification in computer science with a focus on software development. This could be a certificate, diploma or a bachelor degree.

name: Delivery Manager
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in business, commerce, IT or a related field. This usually takes three years of full-time study.

name: DevOps Engineer
qualification: Complete a Bachelor of Computer Science or a related degree that focuses on software development.

name: Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification in computer science with a focus on software development.

name: Digital Business Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in IT, business, marketing or a related field. Aim to secure an internship while studying to gain industry experience.

name: Digital Project Manager
qualification: Consider training in the Agile project management methodology to become a Scrum Master. Agile is the project management methodology of choice in the digital industry.

name: Engineer
qualification: Decide on what type of Engineer you want to be. Although many of the skills of an Engineer are transferable between disciplines, it is recommended that you choose a specialisation early, in order to better focus your studies and training.

name: Enterprise Architect
qualification: Get a bachelor or master’s degree in computer science, information technology or a related field.

name: Front End Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification in Computer Science with a focus on Software Development. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Programming) (ICT40120), a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) or a Bachelor degree majoring in Software Development.

name: Full Stack Developer
qualification: Complete a relevant qualification. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Programming) (ICT40120), Diploma of Information Technology (Back End Web Development) (ICT50220) or Diploma of Information Technology (Front End Web Development) (ICT50220).  Alternatively, you could complete a more advanced qualification, such as a bachelor degree in IT or computer science.

name: Game Designer
qualification:
Undertake a qualification in the area of game design. This is commonly a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Gaming Development) (ICT40120) or a 
Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220).

name: Game Developer
qualification: The technology in use in the gaming industry evolves constantly. It is important to keep up to date with the programming languages and game engines that are currently in use in the industry and aim to specialise in one of the in-demand programming languages.

name: IT Business Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in business administration, information systems or a related field. Alternatively, for students with previous tertiary qualifications in an unrelated field, complete a postgraduate qualification in business administration or a similar discipline.

name: IT Consultant
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree majoring in Information Technology. This is usually a three–year course of study.

name: IT Manager
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, information technology, IT project management or a related field.

name: IT Project Manager
qualification: Consider completing an undergraduate degree such as the Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Computer Science.

name: IT Support Officer
qualification: Complete a qualification in information technology, or information technology support, such a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50115) or a Bachelor of Information Technology. You’ll usually need a senior secondary school certificate or equivalent to gain entry.

name: IT Support Technician
qualification: Complete a qualification in information technology, or information technology support, such a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50115) or a Bachelor of Information Technology. You’ll usually need a senior secondary school certificate or equivalent to gain entry.

name: IT Technician
qualification: Complete a qualification in Information Technology. This could be the Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50118) or a Bachelor of Information Technology.

name: Information Security Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, programming, or a related field.

name: Infrastructure Project Manager
qualification: Obtain a White Card. You can apply for a White Card online, and it is mandatory to hold one in order to work on a construction site in Australia.

name: Integration Engineer
qualification: Complete a relevant degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Software Engineering. This usually takes three to four years of full-time study.

name: Java Developer
qualification: Complete a relevant degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Software Engineering (Honours). Alternatively, a VET qualification such as a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) can introduce you to some of the skills required for the role.

name: JavaScript Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification in Computer Science with a focus on software development. This could be a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50115) or a Bachelor degree majoring in Software Development.

name: Mobile Application Developer
qualification: Complete a relevant degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Software Engineering. This usually takes three to four years of full-time study.

name: Network Administrator
qualification: Complete a relevant qualification such as a Diploma of Information Technology (Advanced Networking) (ICT50220), or a bachelor degree in information technology or computer science.

name: Network Engineer
qualification: Complete a relevant degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Systems or Bachelor of Information Technology. If you have a previous tertiary qualification in another discipline, consider completing a postgraduate degree in information technology or networking.

name: Network Specialist
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in information technology, computer science or a similar field. This usually takes three years.

name: PHP Developer
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, IT or software engineering. Alternatively, a VET course such as a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) can introduce you to the basic skills required for the role.

name: Penetration Tester
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in cyber security, computer science, information technology or a related field.

name: Portfolio Manager
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in finance, accounting, commerce, economics or business. Selecting subjects that focus on investing, such as risk management, asset management or statistics can give you a solid background in portfolio management.

name: Presales Consultant
qualification: Consider completing a relevant qualification. This could be a degree in business or commerce, or a degree related to your field of work, such as a Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Computer Science.

name: Product Designer
qualification: Complete a qualification in Product Design. This may be a Certificate IV in Design (CUA40715), or Bachelor degree majoring in Product Design. Alternatively, if you already have a degree, you can complete a postgraduate qualification in digital product design or product management.

name: Product Manager
qualification: A qualification in a related discipline may be an advantage, such as IT, computer science, marketing, or business.

name: Product Owner
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in information technology, computer science, business or a related field. This usually takes three years of full-time study.

name: Program Coordinator
qualification: Consider completing a vocational qualification in project management, or a bachelor degree in business or economics.

name: Program Manager
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in business management or economics or in the industry you plan to enter, such as engineering or computer science.

name: Programmer
qualification: Complete a qualification in computer science with a focus on software development. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Programming) (ICT40120), a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) or a Bachelor degree majoring in software development.

name: Project Coordinator
qualification: Complete a qualification in project management. This could be a Certificate IV in Project Management Practice (BSB40920) or a Diploma of Project Management (BSB50820).

name: Project Manager
qualification: Complete a Certificate IV in Project Management Practice (BSB40920). This certificate will prepare you to work as a part of a project team.

name: Project Support Officer
qualification: Consider completing a vocational qualification, such as a Certificate IV in Project Management Practice (BSB40920), or a Diploma of Project Management (BSB50820). These courses provide practical skills and knowledge to prepare you for a career in project management. Alternatively, a short course may provide you with basic knowledge and skills.

name: Reporting Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, IT, data science, finance or economics. This usually takes three years. Seek internship opportunities while studying to gain workplace experience.

name: SQL Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification such a Diploma of Software Development (ICT50715) or a Bachelor degree majoring in Software Development.

name: Salesforce Developer
qualification: Complete a degree in computer science or information technology. Alternatively, a bootcamp or intensive short course may provide you with relevant skills.

name: Scrum Master
qualification: Complete a relevant qualification such as a bachelor degree in business, IT or a related field.

name: Search Engine Optimisation Specialist
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in IT, marketing, commerce or a related field. This usually takes three years of full-time study.

name: Security Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, information technology, cybersecurity or a related field.

name: Service Desk Analyst
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science or information technology. This usually takes three years of full-time study. Alternatively, you could complete a VET qualification, such as a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Systems Administration Support). Courses accredited by the Australia Computer Society are internationally recognised and may offer future opportunities for certification and upskilling.

name: Service Desk Officer
qualification: Complete a qualification in IT. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (ICT40120), which usually takes one year. Alternatively, complete a degree in information technology, computer science or a related field, which usually takes three years and may provide broader career options.

name: Sitecore Developer
qualification: Complete a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Information Technology. This usually takes three years of full-time study.

name: Software Architect
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, software engineering or a related field. This usually takes three to four years of full-time study.

name: Software Developer
qualification: Complete a relevant bachelor degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Engineering (Software) (Honours). Alternatively, a VET qualification such as a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) can introduce you to some of the skills required for the role.

name: Software Engineer
qualification: Complete a relevant bachelor degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Software Engineering. Alternatively, a bootcamp or intensive short course can introduce you to the fundamentals. Degrees accredited by the Australian Computer Society are internationally recognised and may offer future opportunities for certification and upskilling.

name: Solutions Architect
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in a relevant field, such as information technology, information systems, software engineering or computer science.

name: Solutions Designer
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in a relevant field, such as information technology, information systems, software engineering or computer science.

name: Solutions Engineer
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, information technology or software engineering. This usually takes three to four years.

name: Support Analyst
qualification: Complete a tertiary qualification in IT. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (ICT40120) or a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220), which usually take one year. Alternatively, complete a bachelor degree in IT or a related field. This usually takes three years.

name: Support Technician
qualification: Undertake formal qualifications in information technology. This may be through a VET (Vocational Education and Training) course such as a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50118) or a university degree such as the Bachelor of Information Technology.

name: Systems Administrator
qualification: Complete a qualification in Information Technology. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Systems Administration Support) (ICT40120), a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50118) or a bachelor degree majoring in information technology.

name: Systems Analyst
qualification: Complete a Diploma of Information Technology (Systems Analysis) (ICT50220), or an undergraduate degree such as a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Business Administration.

name: Systems Engineer
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in computer science, IT, software engineering, mechanical engineering or a related field.

name: Technical Business Analyst
qualification: Complete a degree relevant to your chosen field of work. This could be a Bachelor of Computer Science, Bachelor of Information Technology or Bachelor of Commerce.

name: Technical Consultant
qualification: Complete a relevant bachelor degree, such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Information Technology. This usually takes three years of full-time study.

name: Technical Lead
qualification: Complete a bachelor degree in a relevant field, such as computer science, IT or software development.

name: Telecommunications Engineer
qualification: Complete a Bachelor of Engineering majoring in Telecommunications Engineering.

name: Testing Analyst
qualification: Complete a relevant bachelor degree. This could be a Bachelor of Computer Science or Bachelor of Information Technology. A VET qualification such as a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) can introduce you to some of the skills required for the role.

name: User Experience Designer
qualification: Develop an eye for design, an understanding of design principles, and learn to identify strengths and weaknesses in user experiences. Consider a short course in UX design, or seek out online or in-person groups to network with other designers and learn from their expertise.

name: User Interface Designer
qualification: Consider completing a short course in graphic design, web design or UX. Alternatively, you can complete a Graduate Certificate in User Experience Design.

name: Web Designer
qualification:
Complete a qualification in Web Design. This may be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Web Development) (ICT40120) or 
Certificate IV in Information Technology (ICT40120), 
Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50220) or Bachelor degree majoring in Web Design.

name: Web Developer
qualification: Complete a qualification in computer science with a focus on web development. This could be a Certificate IV in Information Technology (Web Development) (ICT40120), a Diploma of Information Technology (ICT50120), or a Bachelor degree majoring in website development.
